    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - HOOD, GRILLE, FENDERS AND BUMPER - 8500 - Description
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>Description</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="2">
            <title>BUMPER</title>
            <figure id="f0900601" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0900601.webp" filename="../figg09/g0900601.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                         scalefitwidth="312px" scalefitheight="312px" resolution="200"/>
                <caption>Figure 1. 8500 Series Cab and Chassis</caption>
            </figure>
            <para>The 8500 series front bumper is a stylized wrap around steel bumper assembly with stylized side bumper
                extenders. The wrap around design allows access for the tow eyes, and enhances the air flow to the
                radiator for better engine cooling.
            </para>
            <figure id="f0900602" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/g0900602.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                         scalefitheight="272px" resolution="200"/>
                <caption>Figure 2. Bumper</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. 8500 SERIES BUMPER</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. MOUNTING BOLTS</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <para>The front bumper is a one piece aerodynamically styled steel bumper.</para>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
